description._content: Catalog #: 09_01612 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Aerial view of Grand Canyon taken from aircraft in flight, Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
